https://your-app.railway.app/message/sendText/{{ $json.instanceName }}
```

**B. Update Group ID:**
- Click on **"Prepare WhatsApp Message"** node
- Update `groupId` value to your actual WhatsApp group ID:
```
  120363391136052944@g.us
```

**C. Update Instance Name:**
- In the same node, update `instanceName` to match what you created in Evolution API (default: `mywhatsapp`)

### **Step 4: Set Up Microsoft 365 Credentials**
- Click on **"Get Unread Emails"** node
- Add your Microsoft 365 OAuth2 credentials (same as before)

---

## **PART 6: Test the Workflow**

1. **Send a test email** to your Microsoft 365 account
   - Subject must contain "alert" (or change the filter)
   - Leave it **unread**

2. **Click "Execute Workflow"** in n8n

3. **Check your WhatsApp group** - you should see the message! ðŸŽ‰

---

## **Quick Troubleshooting:**

**If Evolution API URL doesn't work:**
```
POST https://your-app.railway.app/message/sendText/mywhatsapp
Headers: apikey: your-api-key
Body: {
  "number": "120363391136052944@g.us",
  "text": "Test message"
}
